<F P=100> CHINA </F>
<F P=101></F>
<H3> <TI>     Environmental Protection Intensifying in Shanghai </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1411020193 Beijing XINHUA in English 0148 GMT 14 Nov 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW1411020193 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, Nov 14 (XINHUA) -- While enhancing 
environment protection, Shanghai is making efforts to expand 
production of environment protection equipment. 
  Gu Yongbo, deputy director of the Shanghai Municipal Bureau 
of Environment Protection, said that now Shanghai has about 400 
enterprises and institutions engaged in the research, 
development, design and production of environment protection 
facilities with more than 7,000 senior engineers and professors. 
  The scientific development and production of the equipment 
involve nearly all spheres that can be subjected to pollution 
control. 
  By the end of 1992, Shanghai had developed more than 300 
products for pollution control and the total output value of the 
products was about 500 million yuan. 
  Some of the products were exported to developed countries 
include Japan and the United States. 
  Meanwhile, to provide technological data for the government 
to enhance pollution control and promote the development of the 
environment protection industry, the Shanghai Society of 
Environment Sciences has fulfilled a number of scientific 
consultancy programs such as ``the water diverting project on 
the upper reaches of the Huangpu river,'' ``plan for 
comprehensive control of air pollution in Shanghai,'' and 
``forecast on Shanghai's environment in the year 2000.'' 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-41538 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jpten004___94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   JPRS-TEN-94-004 </AU>
Document Type:JPRS 
