<H3> <TI>     Asian Development Bank Assists Environmental Project </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2311174493 Beijing XINHUA in English 1703 GMT 23 Nov 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW2311174493 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Manila, Nov 23 (XINHUA) -- The Asian Development 
Bank has approved a technical assistance grant of 900,000 U.S. 
dollars to China for the second phase of an environmental impact 
assessment (EIA) training project. 
  The aim of the project is to train some 20,000 specialists 
from government departments, companies and institutions in how 
to use the EIA process as a key environmental planning tool. 
  The assistance is financed from the Japan Special Fund. 

</TEXT>

