<H3> <TI>   Government Announces Environmental Aid Project to Indonesia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0512121693 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 1100 GMT 5 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> BK0512121693 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Government has announced the $22 million 
project to help improve environmental management in Indonesia. 
Development Cooperation Minister Gordon Bilney says the project 
will span five years and focus on managing hazardous waste, 
water and air pollution, and coastal water quality. He said 
Indonesia's rapid industrial growth, increasing population, and 
urbanization are resulting in serious environmental problems, 
particularly in East Java. Australian environmental experts 
will provide technical advice, technology support, and training. 

</TEXT>

