<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Seek Environmental Protection Convention </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1511141093 Warsaw PAP in English 1327 GMT 15 Nov 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD1511141093 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Nov 15 -- Minister of Environmental 
Protection, Natural Resources and Forestry Stanislaw Zelichowski 
on Monday announced that Poland will ask the Czech Republic, 
Slovakia, Ukraine and Belarus to sign a convention in which the 
four countries will state they will not implement investment 
projects which are unfriendly to the natural environment of 
their neighbours. 
  Speaking at a press conference, the minister also said that 
``ecology is without frontiers.'' ``The issues of the 
environmental protection are common in our part of Europe and 
therefore, establishing closer cooperation ties with our 
neighbours will be one of the ministry's policies,'' he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

