<H3> <TI>   Arab-Israeli Environment Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   First Practical Breakthrough Reported at Environment Talks </H4>
<F P=102> TA1611060893 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 16 
Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> TA1611060893 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There has been a first practical breakthrough in the 
multilateral talks on environmental issues. A joint 
Jordanian-Israeli mechanism was established at the Cairo 
conference in order to deal with sea pollution in al-'Aqabah and 
to protect the gulf's coral reefs. Our correspondent Shulamit 
Schmerling reports that the other delegations participating in 
the talks, including the World Bank, agreed to help finance the 
joint mechanism. 

</TEXT>

