<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finnish Nuclear Waste Delivered to Chelyabinsk-65 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1511094393 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0630 GMT 
15 Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD1511094393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Twenty-five tonnes of nuclear fuel waste have been 
sent to Chelyabinsk-65 by the Finnish company Imatran Voima OY. 
This is the 11th delivery of the deadly freight from the 
company engaged in nuclear waste disposal. The Mayak production 
association has already received 200 tonnes of waste. According 
to a Norwegian ecological organization, there are about 30 
tonnes of plutonium at Mayak's stores. Russian authorities have 
told the international organization Greenpeace that Mayak does 
not have the necessary licence entitling it to reprocess this 
specific material, and therefore the International Atomic Energy 
Association does not consider itself responsible for supervizing 
the reprocessing of waste. This report was supplied by the 
European-Asian News Agency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

