<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Orders Inspection of Nuclear Sites </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1411141993 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 14 Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD1411141993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report from Murmansk by correspondent G. Smirnova; </F>
from the ``Vesti'' newscast] 
  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has instructed 
Gosatomnadzor [state body supervising nuclear and radiation 
safety] to carry out preventative checks at all nuclear power 
enterprises where there is a potential danger of radiation. 
  Smirnova: A detailed inspection has just been 
finished at the Atomflot [nuclear fleet] technological repair 
yard. An authoritative Gosatomnadzor commission inspected the 
workshops, mooring lines, offices and, particularly carefully, 
the (Imandra) floating technical base, to which nuclear fuel was 
being delivered at the time. 
  The commission had no serious complaints about the work of 
the enterprise's personnel. Its main conclusion coincided with 
the opinion of experts of the Russian-Norwegian expedition which 
studied radioactive pollution in the northern seas. A year ago 
they visited the technological repair yard of the nuclear 
ice-breaker fleet and also reached the conclusion that the 
system of ensuring nuclear and radioactive control there 
corresponds to all requirements and norms of radioactive safety. 
[video shows Atomflot premises; commission's members 
inspecting the enterprise] 

</TEXT>

