<H3> <TI>   Toxic Waste in Ukraine </TI></H3>
<H4>   Environment Minister Claims Imported Toxic Waste Could 
Poison All Life </H4>
<F P=102> AU1911112693 Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER in Ukrainian 16 Nov 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1911112693 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report] </F>
  [Text] Approximately 700 tonnes of toxic waste consisting 
of first-category chemical substances that could poison all 
living organisms have already been brought to Ukraine through 
all sorts of illegal channels, says Yuriy Kostenko, minister of 
environmental protection. In his opinion, the main reason for 
the illegal transportation of the deadly cargo is the absence of 
law that would regulate the procedure for bringing toxic 
substances to our territory. 

