  Concentrations of cadmium, lead, and selenium were twice as 
high near highways in most cities than in residential 
neighborhoods, regardless of the distinctive features of 
industrial production in these cities. 
<H5>  Background Air Pollution </H5>
  The comprehensive background monitoring network now consists 
of six stations located in biosphere preserves: Central-Forest, 
Oka-Terrace, Voronezh, Astrakhan, and Caucasus. 
  Readings over several years indicate air pollution levels in 
the ETR that are 3-10 times as high as in East Siberia. 
Furthermore, in the case of contaminants undergoing 
transformation in the air (sulfur dioxide and benzpyrene), 
average concentrations generally decrease as the pollutants are 
carried to the south, while average concentrations of dust and 
sulfates generally increase, which is particularly apparent from 
the rise in maximum figures. 
  In 1991 the content of heavy metals in the air in most of 
the 
background territories did not change, and the content of sulfur 
and nitrogen compounds also remained at the 1990 levels. 
Background concentrations of DDT and HCCH pesticides continued 
to decrease, particularly in the south of Russia. BP levels 
remained high in the western regions of the ETR: Up to 70 
percent of the samples taken in the cold season exceeded the 
average daily MAC. The content of pollutants in precipitation in 
the background territories was monitored at 15 stations working 
on regional and international programs. 
  The content of heavy metals in precipitation was also 
approximately the same as it had been the previous year. Data on 
heavy metal precipitate in 1992 in milligrams per square 
kilometer in the year are presented in Table 1.2.3. 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Table 1.2.3. Heavy Metal Content of Precipitation in Background Territories  | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Metal                    |ETR                      |ATR                      | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Lead                     |1.2-4.5                  |0.88-9.5                 | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Cadmium                  |0.12-0.98                |0.085-0.45               | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Mercury                  |0.13-0.68                |0.02-0.48                | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Zinc                     |                         |10.0-41.0                | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Copper                   |                         |0.43-5.5                 | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
