Phosphorite ore        93.1*    95.5*    95.2*    95.6*    93.4*    91.5* 


  Complete raw material use is still at a low level. 
Enterprises of the Apatit Association in Murmansk Oblast recover 
only 40 percent of the potential value of apatite-nepheline ore 
in their commercial product. Thousands of tonnes of nepheline 
and titanium are lost with the tailings. The oxidized 
ferruginous quartzite extracted along with ores by mining 
enterprises of the Kursk Magnetic Anomaly are not processed and 
are kept in scrap heaps. Copper, cobalt, and sulfur are not 
recovered from the iron ore in some deposits, noble and 
nonferrous metals and trace elements are not recovered from the 
pyrite concentrates of copper pyrite deposits treated with 
sulfuric acid, and nonferrous metals are not recovered during 
the dressing of tin ores. 


