  According to the Russian State Committee for Statistics, the 
total bag of waterfowl in Russia is 4-5 million a year, but 
experts believe it is 12-13 million. The situation in the tundra 
and forest-tundra zones has remained satisfactory, except for 
the regions of the Bolshaya Zemlya tundra and the Yamal 
Peninsula, where intensive economic development has reduced the 
numbers of some species. In the forest zone there is a tendency 
toward a decrease in numbers everywhere. Even in East Siberia, 
the situation could be described as pre-depressive. The habitats 
of waterfowl in Maritime Kray have changed dramatically. 
  The great variety of Russia's mammals is illustrated in 
Figure 1.7.4. The variety of ungulates and carnivores is 
illustrated separately in figures 1.7.5 and 1.7.6. 


<FIG ID=JPRS-TEN-005-40A>           Figure 1.7.4. Total Number of Species </FIG>





