  Section 10. Summary. Conclusions. Ecological Forecasts and 
Recommendations--Doctor of Biological Sciences N.G. Rybalskiy 
and Candidate of Technical Sciences V.G. Sokolovskiy, science 
editors and supervisors 
  This state report is a collective work by specialists from 
43 
ministries and departments of the Russian Federation, the 
scientists of sectorial research institutes, and the scientists 
of the Russian Academy of Sciences and Russian Academy of 
Agricultural Sciences with expertise in the monitoring and 
analysis of the state of the environment and natural resources, 
the regulation of resource use, the exercise of state ecological 
control over the activities of resource users, and the 
supervision of environmental protection measures. 
  The purpose of the report is the provision of state 
governing 
bodies and the population of Russia with objective, 
systematized, analytical information about environmental 
quality, the state of natural resources, and tendencies toward 
change under the influence of economic activity. The report 
contains information about the legal, organizational, technical, 
and economic measures that are being taken within the territory 
of Russia to protect the environment and conserve and restore 
natural resources and will serve as a basis for the choice of 
priority fields and areas of environmental activity and programs 
to aid in the improvement of ecological conditions in Russia. 
  When the Russian Minprirody was preparing this report, it 
was 
striving to present the most complete and objective description 
of environmental conditions in the Russian Federation in 1992 in 
the interest of ecological safety and stable economic 
development. 
  The specialists who prepared the report, however, are fully 
aware that the information presented in this document is not 
commensurate with the scales and significance of the 
``ecological problem'' and cannot satisfy specialists and the 
public completely. There are several objective and subjective 
reasons for this. We hope that our work on the 1992 state report 
will help us recognize them and surmount them in the future. 
  Nevertheless, the submitted document is an attempt to 
present 
information about the state of the environment in Russia in 1992 
in fairly general and accessible terms and to underscore the 
importance of ecological issues and solutions in Russia today. 
<H5>  List of Compilers of Maps in State Report </H5>
  The following maps were compiled by A.S. Martynov and N.Yu. 
Leonova (VNIIpriroda) with the aid of state statistics--figures 
1-5, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 1.3.5, 1.3.6, 1.4.1, 1.4.2, 1.4.4, and 1.6.1. 
  The following maps were compiled by A.S. Martynov: 
  Figures 1.7.1, 1.7.3, and 1.7.4 with the materials of A.Ye. 
Volkov (VNIIpriroda); 
  Figures 2.1.1 and 2.1.2 with the materials of A.Ye. Volkov 
and I. Lysenko (VNIIpriroda); 
  Figures 1.7.5 and 1.7.6 with the materials of the Animal 
Resource Laboratory (VNIIpriroda). 
  The map illustrating the stability of terrestrial ecosystems 
was compiled by A.S. Martynov and V.V. Artyukhov (Figure 1.7.2). 
  The maps of the compiling teams listed below were coded, 
drawn to scale, and printed by specialists from the Geography 
Department of Moscow State University--N.S. Kasimov, A.M. 
Berlyant, O.R. Musin, S.M. Koshel, V.N. Semin, and V.M. 
Shaforostov. 
  Figures 1.2.4, 1.2.5, and 1.2.6--T.V. Belikova, V.N. 
Vasilenko, I.M. Nazarov, and Sh.D. Fridman; 
  Figure 1.9.1--Yu.A. Izrael (chief editor), Sh.D. Fridman, 
I.M. Nazarov, Ye.V. Kvasnikova, Ye.V. Imshennik, Yu.S. Tsaturov, 
Ye.D. Stukin, R.S. Kontarovich, V.M. Kertsman, A.F. Fedotkin, 
S.I. Avdyushin, N.M. Shusharina, S.M. Vakulovskiy, A.V. Lapin, 
V.V. Martynenko, V.A. Looper, M.V. Nikiforov, V.D. Reshetov, and 
V.V. Chelyukanov; 
  Figure 1.9.2--Yu.A. Izrael (chief editor), Sh.D. Fridman, 
I.M. Nazarov, Ye.V. Kvasnikova, Ye.V. Imshennik, Yu.S. Tsaturov, 
R.S. Kontarovich, V.M. Kertsman, A.F. Fedotkin, S.I. Avdyushin, 
and N.M. Shusharina. 
  The climate maps (figures 1.1.4-1.1.6) were compiled 
anonymously. 
  The coordinating center of the preparatory work on the 
report 
was the Main Administration of Ecological Programs of Russian 
Minprirody: V.G. Zhiboyedov, T.A. Moiseyeva, A.V. Zhirnov, N.S. 
Zhuravleva, N.A. Senatova, and G.V. Chernyshkova. 
  The general project supervisor was Candidate of Economic 
Sciences A.A. Averchenkov. 

